'''Vítor Machado Ferreira''' (born 13 February 2000), known as '''Vitinha''' ({{IPA|pt|viˈtiɲɐ}}), is a Portuguese professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[defensive midfielder]] for [[Ligue 1]] club [[Paris Saint-Germain FC|Paris Saint-Germain]] and the [[Portugal national football team|Portugal national team]]. Considered one of the best midfielders in the world, he is known for his ball control, work rate and playmaking abilities.<ref>{{cite web |last=Maston |first=Tom |date=29 April 2025 |title=Ballon d'Or 2025 Power Rankings: Ousmane Dembele edges ahead of Barcelona trio despite Lamine Yamal's sensational Champions League showing |url=https://www.goal.com/en-ng/lists/ballon-dor-2025-power-rankings/bltd009fae5576d751f#cs260659c9499bd2af |access-date=5 May 2025 |website=Goal.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Watach |first=Nestor |date=17 April 2025 |title=2025 Ballon d'Or power rankings: Mbappe's hopes dealt fatal blow... |url=https://www.planetfootball.com/lists-and-rankings/2025-ballon-dor-power-rankings-mbappe-lewandowski-yamal-haaland |access-date=5 May 2025 |website=Planet Football}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=2025 FC 100: Pedri among best central midfielders in men's soccer |date=4 June 2025 |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/45178073/2025-fc-100-pedri-best-central-midfielders-mens-soccer}}</ref>

Coming through [[FC Porto|Porto]]'s youth system, Vitinha was promoted to the first-team in 2020. He was [[Loan (association football)|loaned]] to [[Premier League]] club [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] in September 2020, before returning the following season. He established himself as an integral player for Porto winning a [[Double (association football)|domestic double]], being named the league's Best Young Player of the Year. In June 2022, he joined Paris Saint-Germain. With PSG, he won four [[Ligue 1]] titles and two [[Coupe de France|Coupes de France]], and was integral to the club winning their first [[UEFA Champions League]] titles back-to-back in [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League|2025]] and [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League|2026]], with the former being part of a [[continental treble]]. In [[2025 Ballon d'Or|2025]], Vitinha finished third in the voting for the [[Ballon d'Or]] award and was included in the [[FIFPRO World 11|FIFPRO World XI]] in 2025.

Vitinha is a former [[Portugal national youth football team|Portugal youth international]], representing his country at various youth levels, being part of [[Portugal national under-17 football team|the under-19]] and [[Portugal national under-21 football team|under-21 team]]s that finished as runners-up in the [[2019 UEFA European Under-19 Championship]] and [[2021 UEFA European Under-21 Championship|2021 European Under-21 Championship]], respectively. He made his senior international debut in 2022, representing Portugal at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] and [[UEFA Euro 2024]]. He won the [[UEFA Nations League]] in [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League|2025]].

==Club career==
===Porto===
====2019–20: Early career====
Vitinha was born in [[Santo Tirso]], [[Porto District]]. He started playing football at [[Clube Desportivo das Aves|Desportivo das Aves]], where his father formerly played for the club, before moving to Pinheirinhos de Ringe, where he played alongside goalkeeper and future international teammate [[Diogo Costa]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Pinheirinhos de Ringe transformaram “o Iraque” em oportunidade|trans-title=Pinheirinhos de Ringe transformed "Iraq" into opportunity|url=https://afporto.pt/noticias/pinheirinhos-de-ringe-transformaram-o-iraque-em-oportunidade/ |access-date=2 December 2025 |publisher=[[Porto Football Association]] |date=23 November 2022 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> After going through some training sessions with [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]], he was integrated into one of Benfica's feeder club Póvoa de Lanhoso, where he stayed for three years.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Lopes |first1=João |title=Vitinha: Não lhe deram 'passe' para o Seixal e vai deixar 40 milhões nos cofres do FC Porto|trans-title=Vitinha: They didn't give him a 'pass' for Seixal and he will leave 40 million in FC Porto's coffers |url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-betclic/fc-porto/detalhe/vitinha-nao-lhe-deram-passe-para-o-seixal-e-vai-deixar-40-milhoes-nos-cofres-do-fc-porto |access-date=2 December 2025 |work=Record |date=15 June 2022 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> Despite [[Sporting CP]] being interested in him, Vitinha ended up joining the youth ranks of [[FC Porto]] two years later, aged eleven, being subsequently loaned to [[Padroense F.C.|Padroense]] for a season.<ref name=career>{{Cite web|url=https://www.publico.pt/2022/03/07/desporto/noticia/vitinha-regresso-inesperado-afirmacao-categorica-1997898|title=Vitinha, um regresso inesperado e uma afirmação categórica|date=7 March 2022 }}</ref>

He made his [[LigaPro]] debut for [[FC Porto B|the reserve team]] on 11 August 2019 in a game against [[S.C. Covilhã|Sporting da Covilhã]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Soccerway|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2019/08/11/portugal/liga-de-honra/sc-covilha/porto-b/3065083/|title=Game Report by Soccerway|date=11 August 2019}}</ref> He was also part of [[FC Porto Juniors|Porto's squad]] that won the [[2018–19 UEFA Youth League]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.dn.pt/desportos/interior/fc-porto-e-campeao-europeu-sub-19-10845534.html|title=FC Porto é campeão Europeu Sub-19|trans-title=FC Porto are Under-19 European champions|newspaper=[[Diário de Notícias]]|first=Isaura|last=Almeida|language=Portuguese|date=29 April 2019|access-date=23 September 2020}}</ref> On 28 January 2020, Vitinha made his first appearance for the first team, coming on as a substitute for [[Wilson Manafá]] in the 61st minute in a match against [[Gil Vicente F.C.|Gil Vicente]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Soccerway|url=https://soccerway.com/matches/2020/01/28/portugal/portuguese-liga-/futebol-clube-do-porto/gil-vicente-fc/3064797|title=Porto vs. Gil Vicente - 28 January 2020|date=28 January 2020}}</ref> He made a total of eight appearances as the club won the league title.<ref name=guardian>{{cite news |title=Juventus held by Sassuolo in thriller, Porto win Primeira Liga title |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2020/jul/16/european-roundup-juventus-sassuolo-milan-parma-porto-sporting |access-date=16 July 2020 |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=16 July 2020}}</ref>

====2020–21: Loan to Wolves====
On 9 September 2020, Vitinha moved on a season-long [[Loan (association football)|loan]] to English [[Premier League]] club [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]].<ref name="Wolves">{{Cite news |title=Wolves sign highly-rated midfielder|url=https://www.wolves.co.uk/news/first-team/20200909-wolves-sign-highly-rated-midfielder/|publisher=Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|date=9 September 2020}}</ref> The club held an option to make the loan into permanent deal at its conclusion for a fee of €20&nbsp;million, as Porto were forced to loan him due to [[UEFA]]'s [[UEFA Financial Fair Play Regulations|Financial Fair Play]] regulations.<ref name="Wolves"/> He made his debut on 14 September away to [[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]] as a second-half substitute,<ref>{{Cite news |title=Sheffield United 0–2 Wolverhampton Wanderers: Nuno praises special Wolves|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/54052534|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|first=Gary|last=Rose|date=14 September 2020}}</ref> and his first start three days later in a home [[EFL Cup]] defeat to [[Stoke City F.C.|Stoke City]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Wolverhampton Wanderers 0–1 Stoke City |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/54097201 |website=BBC Sport |date=17 September 2020}}</ref>

Vitinha made his full Premier League debut away to [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] on 29 December 2020, a game which Wolves lost narrowly to a  deflection in added time.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/55406822|title=Manchester United 1–0 Wolverhampton Wanderers: Marcus Rashford scores late winner|publisher=BBC Sport|first=Simon|last=Stone|date=29 December 2020|access-date=29 December 2020}}</ref> On 22 January, he scored his first goal for the club with a 35-yard strike in a 1–0 away win over non-League team [[Chorley F.C.|Chorley]] in the fourth round of the [[FA Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/55722682|title=Chorley 0–1 Wolverhampton Wanderers: Vitinha's superb goal sees Wolves past non-league opponents|publisher=BBC Sport|first=Simon|last=Stone|date=22 January 2021|access-date=22 January 2021}}</ref> At the end of the season, the club declined to exercise his buy option.<ref name=career/>

====2021–22: Return and domestic double====
Vitinha began the [[2021–22 Primeira Liga|2021–22 season]] on [[Substitute (association football)|the bench]], but following his impressive performances during the [[2021 UEFA European Under-21 Championship]], he began finding more and more space as a starter, scoring his first goal for the club in a 3–0 away win against [[Portimonense S.C.|Portimonense]] on 3 December.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/match-direct/championnat-du-portugal/2021-2022/portimonense-fc-porto-live/518409|title = Portimonense 0-3 FC Porto, Liga Portugal Bwin (Ex Liga Nos), résultat du match (03/12/2021)}}</ref><ref name=career/> On 23 December, Vitinha impressed during the 3–0 home over rivals Benfica in ''[[O Clássico]]'' in the [[Taça de Portugal]], scoring and assisting a goal, as he was named man of match.<ref name=career/>

Shortly after [[Sérgio Oliveira]] departed to [[A.S. Roma|Roma]] in January 2022, Vitinha further consolidated his place as starter, impressing Porto's manager [[Sérgio Conceição]], with his performances without the ball and his pressing, being named the league's Player of the Month and Midfielder of the Month for two consecutive months in December and January, a feat which he repeated in March.<ref name=career/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jn.pt/desporto/vitinha-eleito-medio-e-jogador-do-mes-na-liga-14603049.html|title=Vitinha eleito médio e jogador do mês na Liga|date=18 February 2022 }}</ref>

Vitinha would contribute to 47 appearances, with a goal in the 3–1 defeat of [[C.D. Tondela|Tondela]] in the [[2022 Taça de Portugal Final|domestic cup final]], to help Porto win the [[Double (association football)|domestic double]] of the [[Primeira Liga]] and the [[Taça de Portugal]], while also being named in the [[2021–22 Primeira Liga#Annual awards|Primeira Liga Team of the Year]] and the Primeira Liga Best Young Player of the Year.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |date=23 June 2022 |title=Vitinha integrates the Liga Portugal bwin Team of the Year |url=http://www.ligaportugal.pt/en/epocas/20212022/noticias/geral/onze-do-ano/vitinha-no-11-do-ano-da-liga-portugal-bwin/ |access-date=10 August 2023 |website=Liga Portugal |archive-date=11 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231011191605/https://www.ligaportugal.pt/en/epocas/20212022/noticias/geral/onze-do-ano/vitinha-no-11-do-ano-da-liga-portugal-bwin/ |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name=PL>{{cite web|url=https://portugoal.net/club-news/2577-zaidu-winner-takes-porto-to-the-title-away-to-bitter-rivals-benfica|title=Zaidu winner takes Porto to the title away to bitter rivals Benfica|publisher=PortuGOAL|first=Patrick|last=Ribeiro|date=7 May 2022|access-date=7 May 2022}}</ref><ref name=Double2>{{cite web|url=https://portugoal.net/club-news/2599-taca-de-portugal-final-porto-take-down-tondela-to-seal-domestic-double|title=Taça de Portugal Final: Porto take down Tondela to seal domestic double|first=Jamie|last=Farr|publisher=PortuGOAL|date=22 May 2022|access-date=22 May 2022}}</ref>

===Paris Saint-Germain===
====2022–23: Adaptation to France====
On 30 June 2022, Vitinha signed a five-year contract with [[Ligue 1]] side [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]] (PSG), for a fee of €41.5 million, after triggering the [[release clause]] of his contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/vitinha-joins-paris-saint-germain-through-to-2027|title=Vitinha joins Paris Saint-Germain through to 2027|publisher=Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|date=30 June 2022|access-date=30 June 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/62005016|title=Vitinha: Midfielder joins PSG from Porto for £34m|website=BBC Sport|date=30 June 2022|access-date=30 June 2022}}</ref>

[[File:Vitinha (PSG).jpg|thumb|upright=0.8|Vitinha warming up for [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]] in August 2022]]
Vitinha made his debut for the club on 31 July, starting in PSG's 4–0 victory over [[FC Nantes|Nantes]] in the [[2022 Trophée des Champions|Trophée des Champions]], registering a 100% passing rate, completing 43 out of his 43 passes, while also being booked in the match and winning his first trophy with the club.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/a-final-lots-of-goals-and-a-trophy-a-great-start-to-the-season-match-report-paris-saint-germain-trophee-des-champions-psg-nantes|title=A final, lots of goals and a trophy: a great start to the season!|publisher=Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|date=31 July 2022|access-date=31 July 2022}}</ref> Brought in as a signing for the future, Vitinha was seen as a player that could grow and develop during his tenure with the club and quickly his performances throughout the start of the season were highly lauded, receiving various praises for the central midfield combination of him and [[Marco Verratti]] and his quick adaption into his new team, despite fierce competition from more experienced players like [[Carlos Soler (footballer)|Carlos Soler]], [[Renato Sanches]] and [[Fabián Ruiz]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/fifaplus/en/articles/big-money-signings-battling-for-world-cup-spots-martinez-nunez-phillips-richarlison-tchouameni-vitinha|title=The big-money signings battling for World Cup spots|publisher=[[FIFA]]|date=31 July 2022|access-date=25 October 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ojogo.pt/internacional/liga-campeoes/noticias/marquinhos-admite-surpresa-com-vitinha-e-elogia-um-jogador-do-benfica-15227298.html|title=Marquinhos admite surpresa com Vitinha e elogia um jogador do Benfica|work=O Jogo |publisher=[[O Jogo]]|date=5 October 2022|access-date=25 October 2022}}</ref>

However, the following months, proved to be difficult for him, due to having a complicated relationship with fellow team-mate [[Lionel Messi]] and those close to him in the team, after a reported training ground bust-up between them. He was reportedly the target of [[Neymar]]'s outburst after a 3–1 loss to [[AS Monaco FC|Monaco]] on 11 February 2023, who complained that the squad had been significantly weakened with the arrival of players such as Vitinha. Those incidents took a toll on him and his performances declined on the second half of the season, to the point where he lost his starting spot.<ref name=Improved>{{cite news|url=https://www.getfootballnewsfrance.com/2024/vitinha-from-faltering-form-and-lionel-messi-clash-to-psgs-key-performer/?utm_content=cmp-true|title=VITINHA: FROM FALTERING FORM AND LIONEL MESSI CLASH TO PSG'S KEY PERFORMER|newspaper=Get French Football News|language=en|date=9 April 2024|access-date=29 May 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/revealed-lionel-messi-brutal-blast-psg-team-mate-vitinha/blt5f94c562f4c6cf9b|title=Revealed: Lionel Messi's brutal 'you're bad' blast at ex-PSG team-mate Vitinha that drove midfielder to push for Parc des Princes exit|newspaper=[[Goal.com]]|language=en|date=20 September 2023|access-date=29 May 2024}}</ref>

He scored his first goal for PSG, a long-range strike in a 3–1 home victory over [[RC Lens|Lens]] on 15 April.<ref>{{Cite web |title="I've been searching for that a long time" – Vitinha opens PSG account in style [video] |url=https://portugoal.net/portuguese-abroad/3178-i-ve-been-searching-for-that-a-long-time-vitinha-opens-psg-account-in-style-video#:~:text=Portugal%20international%20Vitinha%20finally%20scored,Lens%20was%20worth%20the%20wait. |access-date=5 May 2023 |website=portugoal.net}}</ref> During [[2022–23 Ligue 1|the season]], he was a key contributor to his team's record 11th [[Ligue 1]] title, despite his irregular form.<ref name="DN">{{cite news|url=https://www.dn.pt/desporto/psg-novamente-campeao-em-franca-com-empate-em-estrasburgo-16431023.html|title=PSG novamente campeão em França com empate em Estrasburgo|trans-title=PSG champions in France again with draw in Strasbourg|newspaper=[[Diário de Notícias]]|language=pt|date=27 May 2023|access-date=28 May 2023}}</ref>

====2023–24: Domestic treble and breakthrough====
The following season, despite the ire and consternations of the senior players, PSG kept their belief in Vitinha and after the departures of Messi and Neymar, his performances improved, gaining fully the trust of new manager [[Luis Enrique]], with his attacking style being put to good use in his system. He also became a popular figure in the dressing room, with his grasp of multiple languages, making him a positive influence that helped unite various factions within the club.<ref name=Improved/> He was named man of the match in PSG's 2–0 win over [[Borussia Dortmund]] on matchday one of the group stage of the [[2023–24 UEFA Champions League]] on 19 September.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Morocco's Achraf Hakimi in UEFA's Team of Week {{!}} MapNews |url=https://www.mapnews.ma/en/actualites/sport/moroccos-achraf-hakimi-uefas-team-week |access-date=25 September 2023 |website=www.mapnews.ma|date=21 September 2023 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=21 September 2023 |title=Morocco's Achraf Hakimi in UEFA's team of week |url=https://en.hespress.com/71417-moroccos-achraf-hakimi-in-uefas-team-of-week.html |access-date=25 September 2023 |website=HESPRESS English - Morocco News |language=en-US}}</ref> On 20 December, he scored his fifth league goal of the season, PSG's first in a 3–1 home victory over [[FC Metz|Metz]], while also maintaining a 90% pass completion rate despite being assigned to a deeper midfield role.<ref name="Goalscoring">{{Cite web |url=https://portugoal.net/portuguese-abroad/3592-vitinha-earning-psg-fans-affection-amid-breakout-goalscoring-season-video |title=Vitinha earning PSG fans' affection amid breakout goalscoring season |access-date=23 December 2023 |date=21 September 2023 |website=PortuGoal}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://apnews.com/article/champions-league-psg-dortmund-65562b5012326f1ce6f273d2dc673f0c |title=Mbappé and Hakimi score as PSG wins 2-0 against Dortmund in Champions League |access-date=11 November 2023 |date=19 September 2023 |website=[[Associated Press]]}}</ref>

On 10 April 2024, Vitinha scored his first Champions League goal in a 3–2 home defeat to [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] in the quarter-finals.<ref>{{Cite web |date=10 April 2024 |title=Paris Saint-Germain 2-3 FC Barcelona |url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/champions-league/2023-2024/paris-saint-germain-v-fc-barcelona-uefa-champions-league-live_sto10095668/story.shtml |access-date=10 April 2024 |website=[[Eurosport]]}}</ref> He scored another goal against Barcelona in the second leg six days later, helping PSG to a 4–1 victory and qualification to the semi-finals.<ref>{{Cite web |date=16 April 2024 |title=Why Barca can only blame themselves after imploding vs. PSG |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/39957062/why-barcelona-only-blame-imploding-vs-psg-champions-league |access-date=16 April 2024 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref> In the semi-finals, PSG was knocked out by Borussia Dortmund, after losing 2–0 on aggregate.<ref>{{cite web |last=Dominski |first=Michael |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/live-blogs/psg-dortmund-live-updates-champions-league-score-result/noPrBVsoDvsb/ |title=PSG vs Dortmund live updates: Bundesliga side into Champions League final after 2-0 aggregate victory. |publisher=The Athletic |date=7 May 2024 }}</ref> Despite the defeat, Vitinha received praise for his performances over both legs, with critics arguing that he was "let down by his teammates".<ref>{{cite web |last=Mackey|first=Ed|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/live-blogs/psg-dortmund-live-updates-champions-league-score-result/noPrBVsoDvsb/0yo8hriiuEcW/|title=PSG ratings: Vitinha let down by disappointing team-mates |publisher=The Athletic|date=7 May 2024}}</ref>

After helping PSG win a [[Treble (association football)|domestic treble]] with record-extending successes in Ligue 1, the [[Coupe de France]], and the [[Trophée des Champions]], he achieved his most prolific season, finishing the campaign with 14 goal involvements (9 goals and five assists), leading Enrique to credit Vitinha as the club's player of the season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ojogo.pt/5932024449/luis-enrique-vitinha-foi-o-melhor-jogador-da-epoca-excecional/|title=Luis Enrique: "Vitinha foi o melhor jogador da época. Excecional"|publisher=[[O Jogo]]|date=26 May 2024}}</ref> His performances throughout the season also saw him being included in [[Trophées UNFP du football#2023–24|Ligue 1's Team of the Year]] and the [[2023–24 UEFA Champions League#Team of the season|Champions League team of the tournament]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Bono |first=Elio |date=13 May 2024 |title=Trophées UNFP : Kylian Mbappé meilleur joueur, le résumé de la soirée |url=https://www.leparisien.fr/sports/football/ligue-1/direct-trophees-unfp-une-5e-recompense-pour-kylian-mbappe-suivez-la-ceremonie-13-05-2024-4GXWIMFU6BHZHIPFQ6RFRSD42I.php |access-date=14 May 2024 |website=leparisien.fr |language=fr-FR}}</ref><ref name="auto">{{Cite web |date=3 June 2024 |title=2023/24 UEFA Champions League Team of the Season |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/028e-1b0b073031ef-cb7193efc2dc-1000--2023-24-uefa-champions-league-team-of-the-season/ |access-date=3 June 2024 |website=UEFA |publisher=Union of European Football Associations |language=en}}</ref>

====2024–25: Continental treble and individual achievements====
[[File:FC Salzburg gegen Paris Saint-Germain UEFA Champions League 64.jpg|thumb|upright=0.8|Vitinha playing for [[Paris Saint-Germain FC|Paris Saint-Germain]] during the 2024–25 season]]
On 22 August, Vitinha was elected by manager Luis Enrique as one of the club's [[Vice-captain (association football)|vice-captains]], due to his status within the team.<ref>{{Cite web |date=24 August 2024 |title=Vitinha em destaque no PSG, na lista para ser um dos capitães de equipa |url=https://www.diariodesantotirso.pt/vitinha-em-destaque-no-psg-na-lista-para-ser-um-dos-capitaes-de-equipa/ |access-date=7 September 2024 |publisher=Diário de Santo Tirso |language=pt}}</ref> He also chose him as the club's main penalty-taker, despite some of his teammates not being pleased with the decision, leading him to rotate with [[Ousmane Dembélé]] on penalty duties. On 1 September, Vitinha opened the scoring from the penalty spot, netting his first goal of the season in a 3–1 away win over [[Lille OSC|Lille]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=1 September 2024 |title=90 Minutes of Class Shown in the Art of Penalty Taking: PSG Triumphs in Lille with Vitinha's Goal and Takes Sole Lead in Ligue 1 |url=https://www.footboom1.com/en/news/football/1766497-90-minutes-of-class-shown-in-the-art-of-penalty-taking-psg-triumphs-in-lille-with-vitinhas-goal-and-takes-sole-lead-in-ligue-1 |access-date=7 September 2024 |publisher=Footboom |language=en}}</ref>

On 9 February 2025, he extended his contract with the club until 2029.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/vitinha-i-love-the-city-i-love-the-club-psg-equipe-premiere-interview-2024-2025 |title=Vitinha: "I love the city, I love the club" |publisher=Paris Saint-Germain FC |date=9 February 2025 }}</ref> Ten days later, in the second leg of the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League knockout phase#Knockout phase play-offs|Champions League knockout phase play-offs]], Vitinha got on the scoresheet in a 7–0 win over fellow Ligue 1 side [[Stade Brestois 29|Brest]], scoring PSG's third goal, and helping his side secure a 10–0 aggregate victory to advance to the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League knockout phase|Champions League round of 16]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=PSG 7–0 Brest: French champions stroll into last 16 with 10–0 aggregate win |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c98y71v52ngt |publisher=BBC |work=BBC Sport |date=19 February 2025 |access-date=19 February 2025}}</ref> On 29 April, he was named man of the match in PSG's 1–0 away win over [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] in the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League knockout phase#semi-finals|Champions League semi-finals first leg]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Benson |first=Ryan |date=29 April 2025 |title=Arsenal 0-1 PSG Stats: Dembélé and Donnarumma Decisive to Give Parisians Advantage |url=https://theanalyst.com/2025/04/arsenal-vs-psg-stats-opta-champions-league |access-date=6 May 2025 |website=Opta Analyst |language=en}}</ref> In the second leg, despite missing a penalty, PSG advanced to their second Champions League final, following a 2–1 home victory.<ref>{{Cite news |date=7 May 2025 |title=Ligue des champions. Passeur décisif contre Arsenal, Ousmane Dembélé s'offre un nouveau record |url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/sport/football/paris-sg/ligue-des-champions-passeur-decisif-contre-arsenal-ousmane-dembele-soffre-un-nouveau-record-71973d64-2b83-11f0-91b6-c53abcaa71f4 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250508123543/https://www.ouest-france.fr/sport/football/paris-sg/ligue-des-champions-passeur-decisif-contre-arsenal-ousmane-dembele-soffre-un-nouveau-record-71973d64-2b83-11f0-91b6-c53abcaa71f4 |archive-date=8 May 2025 |access-date=11 May 2025 |work=Ouest-France.fr |language=fr-FR |url-status=live }}</ref> Having helped PSG secure their 13th Ligue 1 title, he was one of the nominees for the [[Ligue 1 Player of the Year]], and was included in the Ligue 1 Team of the Season.<ref name=":5">{{Cite web |title=Ousmane Dembélé élu meilleur joueur de Ligue 1 pour la première fois aux Trophées UNFP |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Ousmane-dembele-elu-meilleur-joueur-de-ligue-1-pour-la-premiere-fois-aux-trophees-unfp/1561044 |access-date=11 May 2025 |website=L'Équipe |language=fr}}</ref>

On 31 May, he created PSG's first goal and provided an assist to [[Desire Doué]]'s second goal in the [[2025 UEFA Champions League final|Champions League final]] against [[Inter Milan]], which PSG won 5–0, securing their first ever Champions League trophy and completing a [[Treble (association football)|continental treble]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0299-1de41a81a0d8-2cfefc69a802-1000--desire-doue-named-official-2025-uefa-champions-league-final/ |title=Désiré Doué named official 2025 UEFA Champions League final Player of the Match |publisher=UEFA |date=31 May 2025 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=1 June 2025 |title='I have no words' - Champions League final MVP Desire Doue pays tribute to head coach Luis Enrique for trusting PSG star to step into Kylian Mbappe's shoes {{!}} Goal.com English Saudi Arabia |url=https://www.goal.com/en-sa/lists/i-have-no-words-champions-league-final-mvp-desire-doue-pays-tribute-to-head-coach-luis-enrique-for-trusting-psg-star-to-step-into-kylian-mbappe-s-shoes/blta19ecb4df34588aa |access-date=1 June 2025 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-SA}}</ref> Additionally, his performances throughout the season also saw him being included in the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League#Team of the season|Champions League team of the tournament]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/029a-1de594e11846-742ee836b971-1000--2024-25-champions-league-team-of-the-season/|title=2024/25 Champions League Team of the Season|website=[[UEFA]] |publisher=Union of European Football Associations|date=1 June 2025|access-date=1 June 2025}}</ref> On 15 June, Vitinha scored the PSG's first goal in the [[FIFA Club World Cup]], netting the opener in a 4–0 win against [[Atlético Madrid]] in the [[2025 FIFA Club World Cup Group B|2025 FIFA Club World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://iffhs.com/posts/4432 |title=Club World Cup |website=iffhs.com |date=16 June 2025 |access-date=22 June 2025}}</ref> He would help his team reach the [[2025 FIFA Club World Cup final|final]], where they were defeated 3–0 by [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]].<ref name="Sky News">{{cite web |url=https://news.sky.com/story/chelsea-win-fifa-club-world-cup-with-victory-over-psg-as-donald-trump-watches-from-stands-13396284 |title=Chelsea win FIFA Club World Cup with victory over PSG - as Donald Trump presents trophy |publisher=Sky News |date=13 July 2025 }}</ref> He finished the tournament with one goal and two assists, earning the [[FIFA Club World Cup awards#Siler Ball|Silver Ball]] as the tournament's second best player.<ref name="Sky News"/>

====2025–26: Back-to-back Champions League titles and Ballon d'Or third place====
On 7 August, Vitinha was one of nine PSG players included in the final 30-man shortlist for the [[2025 Ballon d'Or]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/ballondor/news/029c-1e6c441438f3-f4ffe2b42288-1000--2025-ballon-d-or-awards-nominees-revealed/|title=2025 Ballon d'Or awards nominees revealed|website= UEFA |date=7 August 2025 }}</ref> On 22 September, he finished third in the Ballon d'Or, behind winner and teammate Ousmane Dembélé and [[Lamine Yamal]].<ref name="2025 Ballon d'Or">{{Cite web |title=Ballon d'Or 2025 LIVE: Winners, times & updates from ceremony in Paris |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cdr6kzzlzn0t |access-date=22 September 2025 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> On 5 October, he made his 100th Ligue 1 appearance for PSG in 1–1 draw against Lille.<ref>{{cite web|title=Vitinha reaches 100 Ligue 1 matches with PSG|date=6 October 2025|publisher=Tribuna.com|url=https://tribuna.com/en/news/2025-10-06-vitinha-reaches-100-ligue-1-matches-with-psg/|access-date=27 November 2025}}</ref> In the [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League league phase|Champions League league phase]], on 26 November, Vitinha scored his first career [[List of UEFA Champions League hat-tricks|hat-trick]] in a 5–3 home win against [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]].<ref>{{cite web|title=PSG vs Tottenham highlights as Randal Kolo Muani nets brace in sloppy Champions League defeat|date=26 November 2025|publisher=Football London|url=https://www.football.london/tottenham-hotspur-fc/news/psg-vs-tottenham-live-kick-32948995|access-date=26 November 2025}}</ref> On 17 December, he helped PSG defeat [[CR Flamengo|Flamengo]] 2–1 on penalties, successfully converting his spot kick, in the [[2025 FIFA Intercontinental Cup final|FIFA Intercontinental Cup final]] after a 1–1 draw in regular time, securing his club's first title in the competition. With his performance, Vitinha received the Player of the Tournament and Golden Ball awards.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.france24.com/en/sport/20251217-safonov-saves-four-penalties-as-psg-beat-flamengo-to-win-intercontinental-cup |title=Safonov saves four penalties as PSG beat Flamengo to win Intercontinental Cup |publisher=France 24 |date=17 December 2025 }}</ref>

On 8 January 2026, Vitinha assisted the first goal and created the assist for the second in a 2–2 draw against [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]], as part of ''[[Le Classique]]'' in the [[2025 Trophée des Champions]], an eventual victory on penalties for PSG.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |title=Paris Saint-Germain triumphs over Olympique de Marseille: goals and drama all the way to penalties in the Trophée des Champions |url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/trophe-des-champions/articles/paris-saint-germain-triumphs-over-olympique-de-marseille-goals-and-drama-all-the-way-to-penalties-in-the-troph%C3%A9e-des-champions-2026-01-08 |access-date=17 January 2026 |website=beIN SPORTS |language=en-us}}</ref> Over the following months, he was heavily speculated of a possible transfer to [[Real Madrid]] in the summer. However, on 6 March, in an interview with [[Canal 11 (Portugal)|Canal 11]], Vitinha ruled out any pontential transfer move, reaffirming his intention to continue at PSG, based on the success achieved in the previous season at the club and his positive relationship with his teammates and manager Luis Enrique.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.abola.pt/noticias/vitinha-no-real-madrid-ficou-mais-facil-2026022419315235301 |title=Vitinha no Real Madrid ficou... mais fácil |publisher=A Bola |date=24 February 2026 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://cadenaser.com/nacional/2026/02/24/el-real-madrid-prepara-las-llegadas-de-vitinha-y-sergio-de-larrea-para-el-proximo-mercado-de-fichajes-cadena-ser/ |title=El Real Madrid prepara las llegadas de Vitinha y Sergio de Larrea para el próximo mercado de fichajes |publisher=Cadena SER |date=24 February 2026 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/articles/vitinha-shuts-down-real-madrid-151500099.html |title=Vitinha Shuts Down Real Madrid Transfer Rumors |publisher=Yahoo Sports / PSG Talk |date=6 March 2026 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/48119927/vitinha-foolish-leave-psg-real-madrid-rumour |title=Vitinha: 'Foolish' to leave PSG despite Real Madrid rumour |publisher=ESPN |date=6 March 2026 }}</ref>

On 19 April, in a match against [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]], he suffered an inflammation of his right heel, forcing him to miss PSG's next league matches against [[FC Nantes|Nantes]] and [[SCO Angers|Angers]] and with his availability for the [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League knockout phase|Champions League semifinal]] first leg against [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] on 28 April also being in doubt.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/is-he-fit-for-the-champions-league-clash-with-fc-bayern-munich-psg-has-revealed-the-diagnosis-for-its-injured-star/blta6c1a495552cd109 |title=Is he fit for the Champions League clash with FC Bayern Munich? PSG has revealed the diagnosis for its injured star |publisher=Goal.com |date=20 April 2026 }}</ref> However, he managed to return in time for the tie, helping his team advance to their second consecutive [[2026 UEFA Champions League final|Champions League final]], following a 6–5 aggregate win against them on 6 May.<ref>{{cite web |last=McNulty |first=Phil |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/ce3py2d7dwvt |title=Bayern Munich 1–1 Paris Saint-Germain |publisher=BBC Sport |date=6 May 2026 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Riley |first=Martha |url=https://talksport.com/football/4237425/arsenal-psg-champions-league-final-harry-kane-record/ |title=Arsenal to face Paris Saint-Germain in Champions League final as Harry Kane equals stunning record |publisher=talkSPORT |date=6 May 2026 }}</ref> On 13 May, PSG won 2–0 away against [[RC Lens|Lens]], to secure their 12th league title in 14 years.<ref>{{cite web |title=Grâce à un grand Safonov, le PSG s'impose à Lens et décroche son 14e titre de champion de France |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Grace-a-un-grand-safonov-le-psg-s-impose-a-lens-et-decroche-son-14e-titre-de-champion-de-france/1675604 |website=L’Equipe |language=fr |access-date=13 May 2026}}</ref> Later that month, on 30 May, he was named Player of the Match in the Champions League final against [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]], which Paris Saint-Germain won 4–3 on penalties after a 1–1 draw following extra time, retaining their title.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/02a5-20c0324a93c4-a269d65f5aeb-1000/ |title=Vitinha named official 2026 UEFA Champions League final Player of the Match |publisher=[[UEFA]] |date=30 May 2026 |access-date=30 May 2026}}</ref>

==International career==
===Youth===
Having played at various youth levels for Portugal, Vitinha was named [[Captain (association football)|captain]] for the [[Portugal national under-19 football team|under-19]] squad at the [[2019 UEFA European Under-19 Championship]] in Armenia, playing all five matches, scoring twice and assisting once as the team finished runners-up to [[Spain national under-19 football team|Spain]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.uefa.com/under19/news/0257-0dee769d9719-c61a7e965fcc-1000--spain-win-2019-u19-euro-at-a-glance/|title=Spain win 2019 U19 EURO: at a glance|date=27 July 2019|accessdate=31 July 2019}}</ref>

Vitinha was named in the [[Portugal national under-21 football team|under-21 squad]] for the [[2021 UEFA European Under-21 Championship]]. He was named for the [[2021 UEFA European Under-21 Championship#Team of the tournament|team of the tournament]] as Portugal finished as runners-up after losing in the final 1–0 to [[Germany national under-21 football team|Germany]], on 6 June 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|date=6 June 2021|title=Highlights, report: Germany beat Portugal for third U21 EURO title|url=https://www.uefa.com/under21/news/026a-127532d17acc-e079bf3c8a1c-1000--highlights-report-germany-beat-portugal-for-third-u21-euro-/|access-date=7 June 2021|website=[[UEFA]]}}</ref>

===Senior===
On 21 March 2022, Vitinha received his first call-up to the [[Portugal national football team|senior squad]] for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA second round|2022 World Cup qualification play-offs]], as a replacement for the injured [[Rúben Neves]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fpf.pt/pt/News/Todas-as-not%C3%ADcias/Not%C3%ADcia/news/33848/|title=Vitinha convocado|publisher=[[Portuguese Football Federation]]|date=20 March 2022|language=pt}}</ref> Eight days later at his club ground, he made his senior national team debut, replacing [[João Moutinho]] in added time in a 2–0 victory over [[North Macedonia national football team|North Macedonia]] in the [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA second round|play-off final]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Fernandes |first1=Mariana |last2=Paredes |first2=Diogo |title=Portugal vence Macedónia do Norte com bis de Bruno Fernandes e está no Mundial do Qatar (2-0) - como aconteceu|trans-title=Portugal defeat North Macedonia with a brace from Bruno Fernandes and are in the World Cup in Qatar (2-0) - how it happened |url=https://observador.pt/liveblogs/portugal-macedonia-do-norte-danilo-mantem-se-a-central-ao-lado-de-pepe-diogo-costa-volta-a-ser-titular-na-baliza/ |access-date=29 March 2022 |work=Observador |date=29 March 2022 |language=Portuguese}}</ref>

In October, he was named in Portugal's preliminary 55-man [[Portugal national football team|squad]] for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] in Qatar,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/selecoes/detalhe/cmtv-revela-lista-de-pre-convocados-para-o-mundial2022-conheca-todos-os-nomes?ref=HP_DestaquesPrincipais|title=The list of pre-selected squad for the 2022 World Cup: know all the names|publisher=[[Record (Portuguese newspaper)|Record]]|access-date=31 October 2022|date=23 October 2022}}</ref> being included in the final 26-man squad for the tournament.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/mundial/artigos/os-26-convocados-de-portugal-para-o-mundial2022|title=Os 26 convocados de Portugal: Gonçalo Ramos, António Silva, Otávio e Matheus Nunes chamados|trans-title=Portugal select 26: Gonçalo Ramos, António Silva, Otávio and Matheus Nunes called|publisher=SAPO|language=pt|date=10 November 2022|access-date=10 November 2022}}</ref> He only started in the 2–1 loss to [[South Korea national football team|South Korea]] in Portugal's final group stage match, and appeared off the bench in two knockout-phase matches, in an eventual quarter-final exit.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/63657472|title=Portugal 3−2 Ghana|publisher=BBC Sport|first=Shamoon|last=Hafez|date=24 November 2022|access-date=17 October 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/63698279|title=Portugal 2−0 Uruguay|publisher=BBC Sport|first=Phil|last=McNulty|date=28 November 2022|access-date=17 October 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/63752148|title=South Korea 2−1 Portugal|publisher=BBC Sport|first=Chris|last=Bevan|date=2 December 2022|access-date=17 October 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2022/dec/10/morocco-portugal-world-cup-2022-quarter-final-live|title=Morocco 1−0 Portugal: World Cup 2022 quarter-final – as it happened|newspaper=The Guardian|first=Barry|last=Glendenning|date=10 December 2022|access-date=16 October 2023}}</ref>

[[File:Vitinha, Euro2024 (Agência Lusa).png|thumb|upright=0.8|Vitinha with [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] in 2024]]
On 21 May 2024, he was selected in the 26-man squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite news |date=21 May 2024 |title=Convocados para o Euro 2024 |trans-title=Called up for Euro 2024 |url=https://www.fpf.pt/pt/News/Todas-as-not%C3%ADcias/Not%C3%ADcia/news/45104 |language=pt |publisher=[[Portuguese Football Federation]] |access-date=21 May 2024}}</ref> In the opening match against the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic]], on 18 June, after being one goal down, Vitinha created [[Robin Hranáč]]'s [[own goal]], following a cross to [[Nuno Mendes (footballer, born 2002)|Nuno Mendes]] at the back post, in a 2–1 comeback victory for Portugal, being awarded player of the match.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/report/_/gameId/690584|title=Portugal 2-1 Czechia(June 18, 2024)|publisher=ESPN|date=18 June 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://dailysports.net/news/vitinha-is-the-best-player-of-the-portugal-czech-republic-match-according-to-dailysports/|title=Vitinha is the best player of the Portugal - Czech Republic match according to Dailysports|publisher=Dailysports|date=18 June 2024}}</ref> His performances earned him a spot in the starting eleven, despite fierce competition from teammates [[Bernardo Silva]] and [[Bruno Fernandes]], leading him to start in Portugal's 3–0 win against [[Turkey national football team|Turkey]] on 22 June, helping his country secure qualification to the [[UEFA Euro 2024 knockout phase|knockout phase]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://en.as.com/soccer/cristiano-ronaldo-continues-to-break-records-n/ |title=Cristiano Ronaldo continues to break records |website=en.as.com|date=22 June 2024 |access-date=22 June 2024 }}</ref> He made his third appearance of the tournament in Portugal's [[UEFA Euro 2024 knockout stage#Round of 16|round of 16]] match against [[Slovenia national football team|Slovenia]] and played 65 minutes before being substituted for [[Diogo Jota]] as Portugal won 3–0 in a [[penalty shootout]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/match/2036201--portugal-vs-slovenia/lineups/|title=Portugal vs Slovenia: Line-ups|access-date=3 July 2024|website=UEFA}}</ref> Portugal were eliminated in the quarter-finals to [[France national football team|France]] after losing 5–3 in another penalty shootout.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cy79llev4znt|title=Portugal 0–0 France (France win 5–3 on pens)|publisher=BBC Sport|first=Emma|last=Sanders|date=5 July 2024|access-date=6 July 2024}}</ref>

In May 2025, Vitinha was selected for Portugal’s [[2025 UEFA Nations League Finals]] [[2025 UEFA Nations League Finals squads#Portugal|squad]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Convocatória para Liga das Nações divulgada |trans-title=Nations League squad announced |url=https://www.fpf.pt/pt/News/Todas-as-notícias/Notícia/news/50645 |website=[[Portuguese Football Federation]] |language=pt |access-date=26 May 2025 |date=20 May 2025}}</ref> He and his team would go on to win the tournament [[2025 UEFA Nations League final|5–3 in a penalty shootout]] over rivals [[Spain national football team|Spain]], converting Portugal's second penalty in the shoot-out.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6408339/2025/06/08/spain-portugal-yamal-mendes-ronaldo/|title=Spain 2 Portugal 2 (3–5 on pens): Mendes vs Yamal, Ronaldo being Ronaldo, and World Cup chances|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|first1=Tim|last1=Spiers|first2=Dermot|last2=Corrigan|first3=Stu|last3=James|date=8 June 2025|access-date=8 June 2025}}</ref>

==Style of play==
